cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this replication package, please cite it as below."
title: "Schema-to-Ontology Mapping with LLMs — Replication Package"
abstract: >-
  Replication package for a two-stage evaluation of LLM-assisted mapping of
  relational ERD schemas to domain ontologies, and cross-ERD ontology
  integration, against expert ground truth. Includes the ERD schemas, expert
  ground-truth ontologies, instance data, prompts and briefs, runnable
  evaluation scripts, and the published outputs of the reported runs.
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: "Guimarães"
    given-names: "Pedro"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3390-8528"
date-released: "2026-06-29"
version: "1.0.0"
license: MIT                # code; data/docs are CC-BY-4.0 (see LICENSE-DATA)
repository-code: "<add repository URL>"   # TODO: replace with the repository URL
keywords:
  - ontology engineering
  - schema-to-ontology mapping
  - large language models
  - ontology matching
  - cross-ERD integration
  - reproducibility
references:
  - type: software
    title: "Google Gemini 2.5 Flash"
    notes: "LLM used for the reported runs; model id gemini-2.5-flash, runs dated 2026-06-29, temperature 0.2."
